Another thrilling night!

After slashing interest rates and super-quantitative easing policy lapsed, the Federal Reserve once again pulled out the big guns, the U. S. government is also actively preparing a trillion-dollar stimulus plan to start the era of "helicopter money. ".

After the news, yesterday evening fell below 20,000 points in the Dow began a violent rally, the NASDAQ INDEX, the S & P 500 index has bottomed out, the US stock market staged a great comeback. By the end of the day, the Dow was up more than 5% , the index was up more than 1,000 points, and both the Nasdaq and S & P 500 were up more than 6% .

In the US counter-offensive, European stocks rose rapidly in the last session, Germany, France, the United Kingdom and other major stock market indexes closed up more than 2% . SHORT-SELLING BANS have been renewed in Italy and France, and governments around the world have begun aggressive bail-outs.

A v-shaped rally in U.S. stocks

The Dow closed up over 1,000 points

After a prolonged slump, U.S. stocks are finally getting some breathing room.

Last night, the U. S. stock market staged a v-shaped rally. U.S. stocks opened higher, but then all three indexes turned green and the panic continued, with the Dow falling below 20,000, erasing all of Donald Trump's gains.

However, half an hour later, the U. S. stocks began to bottom rebound, the Dow began to lift violence, the intraday rise of more than 7% . NASDAQ, the Standard & Poor's 500 index has bottomed out, the strength of the Jedi counterattack fierce.

By the end of the day, the Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 5.2% at 21,237.38, the NASDAQ was up 6.23% at 7,334.78 and the S & P 500 was up 6% at 2,529.19.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Popular U.S. stocks rose, with apple up 4.40% , Amazon up 7.03% , google up 3.27% , Facebook up 2.34% , microsoft up 8.23% , tesla down 3.34% , qualcomm up 6.79% , nvidia up 10.63% and AMD up 8.19% .

The U.S. was prepared to offer financial aid to the airline industry, but airline stocks ended down, with United Airlines down 13.25% , delta down 11.34% and Boeing down 4.31% .

U. S. anti-epidemic concept stocks generally rose. Pfizer said it is working with German biotech BioNTech to develop a potential vaccine against the virus, with BioNTech up 62.77% and Pfizer up 6.73% . MODERNA UP 7.05% . mRNA-1273, an anti-viral vaccine developed by Moderna, has begun clinical trials.

Chinese stocks rebounded, Wanda sports up 23% , XUNLEI UP 18% , happy times up 15% .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sentiment eased slightly, with the fear gauge VIX falling 8.2% to 75.91.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Meanwhile, international oil prices fell across the board, with ICE WTI crude falling 2.86 per cent to $32.63 a barrel and cloth oil falling 3.76 per cent to $30.50 a barrel. The news that Saudi Arabia will boost crude exports to an all-time high of 10m b / d added to the slump.

Federal Reserve raises the specter of crisis

Re-launch of commercial paper financing mechanism

This time around, the Fed is finally playing its part.

Last night, the Federal Reserve announced it would establish a commercial paper facility (CPFF) to support the flow of credit to households and businesses.

The commercial paper market has been under "considerable pressure" as a result of the outbreak, the Fed said in a statement. The commercial paper facility should eliminate market risks and improve the ability of businesses to maintain employment and investment during the outbreak, the Treasury will provide $10 billion in credit protection to the Fed from the Treasury's Foreign Exchange Stabilization Fund, which will expire on 2021 unless extended.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is understood that the commercial paper financing mechanism will provide liquidity support to US commercial paper issuers through the special purpose vehicle (SPV) , the tool will purchase unsecured and asset-backed commercial paper with a rating of A1 / P1(as of 17 March 2020) directly from eligible companies.

The commercial paper market has been under considerable pressure in recent days as a result of the COVID-19 outbreak and greater uncertainty for businesses and households. By eliminating the risk that qualified issuers will not be able to roll over maturing commercial paper debt, this mechanism should encourage investors to re-engage in fixed-term lending in the commercial paper market.

The Fed created the commercial paper facility in October 2008 to buy commercial paper from corporate issuers and restore confidence. Since then, outstanding commercial paper has fallen below $1 trillion, but usage has increased again in recent years. The move marks the first time since the Great Depression that the Fed has bypassed banks and lent directly to US companies.

Analysts said the market reacted strongly to the move because it believed it was the most effective measure to ease the market's "dollar shortage. " Companies rely on the commercial paper market as a reliable source of short-term cash to meet unexpected funding needs.

In addition to the Federal Reserve, The New York Fed is also active in the rescue operation. The New York Fed said yesterday after the US stock market opened that it would carry out additional overnight repo operations of up to $500bn. As recently as Monday, The New York Fed made additional overnight repurchases of up to $500 billion.

The New York Fed is understood to be offering one trillion a day through an overnight repo operation this week. The New York fed statement said the move was intended to "ensure adequate provision of reserves and support the smooth functioning of the short-term dollar funding market" .

US One trillion stimulus package

Launch of the helicopter money era

In addition to the Fed's big move, the market is even more excited about the possibility of a "helicopter money" era.

According to Chinanews.com, United States Secretary of the Treasury Tuesday went to Congress to discuss the third round of the new coronavirus response with Senate Republicans in order to ward off the economic crisis caused by the outbreak. The Donald Trump administration wants to implement an $850 billion stimulus package, the report said. The White House proposal would include about $50 billion in aid for the airline industry, according to The Washington Post.

MNUCHIN said the details of the next package would include earlier approval of Fed Chairman Powell's request to use the rediscount window; the Fed's Commercial Paper facility would support a $1 trillion credit market; US President Donald Trump has called for a $300bn tax deferral;

MNUCHIN says if nothing is done, the new pneumonia could cause unemployment to soar to 20 percent.

MNUCHIN said he could "issue a check" to Americans within the next two weeks. For Americans, he said, a "check" would be considered a "business interruption payment. ". When asked who would receive a check, DONALD TRUMP said most Americans would, but people who "make one million bucks a year" probably wouldn't, "and I hope Americans get it soon. " .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
MNUCHIN insisted that the market would not be shut down by the coronavirus and that the banks would remain open even if they set up short hours. "The only reason the market was closed after 9 / 11 was because of the destruction of technology, but Americans should know that we will do everything we can to ensure that Americans have access to their stocks, 401s and the money in their portfolios. "

Can the American "Lehman" script work?

U.S. stocks may still be volatile

But it remains to be seen whether the Federal Reserve and the government, in a series of aggressive stimulus packages and even the financial killing devices of the 2008 financial crisis, will be effective enough to stop US stocks from falling further.

Joseph Stiglitz, a Sveriges Riksbank Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel scholar, argues that the Fed's aggressive policy actions are not enough to help the US avoid a recession caused by a coronavirus outbreak. "given the uncertainty, and given the fact that so many people are losing income, it could at best help stabilise financial markets, but clearly it hasn't even done that. "

"The new coronavirus doesn't scare me, but the new coronavirus epidemic and the long-term interest rate drop to zero worries me, " said Ray Dalio, founder of bridgewater, the world's largest hedge fund, the most targeted and appropriately sized fiscal and monetary response comes from China. In his view, a fall in long-term interest rates to the floor of 0 per cent would mean that almost all asset classes would fall because the positive effects of a fall in interest rates would be gone, at least for a while.

Goldman Sachs said the liquidity of U.S. stocks has reached its worst level since the financial crisis, and the bid-ask spreads offered by U.S. market makers are rocketing, the S & P 500 futures market is also at its lowest level of market depth ever.

The Fed's "Reyman scenario" suggests that the US is now facing systemic risks, including banks and companies, that did not exist before, Zerohedge said. That could lead to a sharp sell-off after a brief upswing, and the market needs to see what other ammunition the Fed has left.

In other news, Chichang recently said that the U.S. stock market's circuit breaker mechanism may be adjusted; suggested that the U.S. stock market's circuit breaker mechanism be adjusted to a 7% and 13% decline limit; and proposed that the ETF market be subject to the same rules as other markets, follow the same fusing rules. The NYSE is proposing to change the rules for three-stage fuses and to suspend trading after the S & P 500 has moved 20 per cent.

U.S. stock futures fell again at about 7:50 a.m. today, with major index futures down more than 3 percent, suggesting that the U.S. rally could be short-lived.

European stocks pull higher in late trading

Many countries launch rescue plans

In the U. S. counterattack led by the European stock market also appeared in the late-day pull up situation.

By the end of the day, Germany's DAX, Britain's FTSE 100 and France's CAC 40 were all up more than 2% .

Several more European countries have joined the "No short selling" queue in an effort to stem the market's slide.

Several European countries have introduced short-selling bans, including France, which will ban short-selling for 24 hours, Belgium's financial regulator, which bans short-selling and similar trades, and Italy's securities and Exchange Commission, which has imposed a short-selling ban, sHORT-SELLING OF 20 Italian Stock Exchanges is banned; the UAE will limit daily losses to 5 per cent from March 18. The Philippines also temporarily closed its financial markets, becoming the first country in the world to do so because of the spread of the new coronavirus.

In addition, a growing number of government bail-outs are in the pipeline. Canadian Prime Minister Trudo is set to announce a stimulus package worth more than C $25 billion, the CBC Television reported.

Separately, the RBA pumped a $10.7 billion into the market through daily market operations, a record high. Australian Prime Minister Morrison said the government was considering further economic measures, with the Central Bank participating in discussions on the measures, which will focus on cushioning the impact and will be announced when new measures are in place.

All 50 states were lost

The global epidemic continues to escalate

However, the current global epidemic is still very serious, adding to market concerns.

All 50 states have fallen as West Virginia has its first confirmed case of pneumonia, AP reported. According to Real time statistics released by the Johns Hopkins University, as of 18:00 EDT, the cumulative number of new cases of pneumonia in the United States was 5,894,97 deaths. Secretary of State Pompeo said some State Department employees had tested positive for the new coronavirus.

As of 4:00 a.m. on March 18,9,257 cases of new coronavirus pneumonia had been confirmed in Germany, including 24 deaths, according to the Johns Hopkins University.

According to Bno News, there were 3526 new cases of pneumonia in Italy, 31506 confirmed cases, 345 new deaths and 2503 cumulative deaths.

According to the Department of Health and Labour protection, as of 9:00 am local time on the 17th, test results showed that 407 new cases of pneumonia in the United Kingdom, a total of 1,950 confirmed cases.

The Iranian Ministry of Health announced on March 17 that in the past day there were 1178 new cases of coronary pneumonia in Iran, bringing the total to 16169, and 135 new deaths, bringing the total to 988.5,389 people have been cured.

As of 00:00 local time on the 17th, there were 84 new confirmed cases of pneumonia in South Korea compared with 00:00 on the 16th, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 8320.

But progress is also accelerating in the United States. A new coronavirus vaccine developed in the United States began the first phase of clinical trials that day, with the first volunteer to be enrolled receiving the experimental vaccine, the National Institutes of Health reported Monday.

Volunteers will receive two intramuscular injections of the experimental vaccine, about 28 days apart, Antony, director of the Institute of Medical Science, said at a White House news conference Thursday. They were divided into three groups and injected with doses of 25,100 and 250 micrograms, respectively, to assess the safety of the different doses and their ability to induce an immune response.

According to reports, the volunteers will receive a one-year observation after completing two injections of the vaccine.

Foutch said the speed with which the first phase of clinical trials of the vaccine was being launched was record. The clinical trial is a crucial first step toward developing a safe and effective vaccine, which is a top priority in the fight against new coronavirus infections.

##Basketball Star Durant tested positive

Chinanews.com, March 18, according to U.S. media reports, NBA Brooklyn Nets players Kevin Durant test positive for the new coronavirus. Durant told reporters he was feeling fine.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is reported that the nets and three other players were also tested positive for the new coronavirus. So far, seven NBA players have been infected with the new coronavirus.

##U.S. State Department finds multiple positive cases

On the afternoon of March 17, U.S. Secretary of State Pompeo said there had been a number of new cases of pneumonia in the U.S. State Department that tested positive.

POMPEO did not give a specific number, but said "one hand can count" . At present, the U. S. State Department has been in accordance with the relevant requirements of the infected personnel to deal with, and will not delay the State Department's functions.
